history.content:
Hello!

Proposed pre-reqs for EE 142 are currently being reviewed by COCI. We expect to hear back from them any day now. The proposed pre-reqs are EE 16A & B, and EE 105. These would go into effect beginning Spring 2017.

Hi as someone taking EE142 this semester, I think EE20 will suffice. However, this is a very heavy load class with assumption of very good working knowledge in both circuits and signals, semiconductor physics and electromagnetics. Therefore, I would suggest a prereq of EE140, EE117, EE130 and EE120 (EE20 may be good enough). Also I think this is a strictly senior level class although you could potentially take it in your junior year if you have very strong fundamentals. That being said, this is a very good class for any EE major. (Best class for me!)
I've seen that EE120 is a prereq for EE142, but other sources list EE20 as a prereq instead of 120. What is the official prereq? How necessary is taking 120, as opposed to 20, for EE142?
